article.headline: Long Island U. 75, Monmouth, N.J. 65
article.story: WEST LONG BRANCH, N.J. (AP) -- Senior Kellen Allen scored a career-high 25 points and Long Island U. defeated Monmouth, N.J. 75-65 on Saturday night. The win clinched a spot in the Northeast Conference Tournament for the Blackbirds (14-13, 6-10 NEC). Monmouth (6-22, 3-13) led at times during the first period, but trailed through most of the game. Jaytornah Wisseh scored 20 points for Long Island. Eugene Kotorobai made 13 points, including three three-pointers. Alex Nunner and Whitney Coleman were the lead scorers for the Hawks, with 11 points each. James Hett and R.J. Rutledge each had 10 points.
